---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const datePublished = '2026-07-13';
const dateModified = '2026-07-13';
---

<Layout
  title="Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy | Wolvec"
  description="Wolvec's Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy, addressing consumer health data under the Washington My Health My Data Act and other applicable consumer health data laws."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebPage",
      "name": "Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy",
      "url": "https://wolvec.ai/consumer-health-data",
      "datePublished": datePublished,
      "dateModified": dateModified,
      "publisher": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Wolvec L.L.C."
      }
    })} />
  </Fragment>
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mb-2">Wolvec L.L.C., a Wyoming limited liability company</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mb-8">
        Effective Date: <time datetime={datePublished}>July 13, 2026</time>
        &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
        Last Updated: <time datetime={dateModified}>July 13, 2026</time>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy describes how Wolvec L.L.C. ("Wolvec," "Company," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, shares, protects, and retains consumer health data.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This Policy applies to individuals who use the Wolvec platform in an individual or household capacity, including clients of fitness coaches who use Wolvec. It supplements Wolvec's general Privacy Policy, which governs all other personal information we collect.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This Policy is intended to address consumer-health-data obligations under laws that may apply to Wolvec's fitness and wellness technology platform, including the Washington My Health My Data Act, Nevada consumer health data law, the Connecticut Data Privacy Act, and California health privacy laws where applicable.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec is a fitness and wellness technology platform. Wolvec is not a medical provider, health plan, healthcare clearinghouse, physical therapy provider, mental health provider, or dietetics provider. Nothing in this Policy or on the Wolvec platform constitutes medical advice, diagnosis, treatment, physical therapy, mental health counseling, or emergency support.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Contact: <a href="mailto:privacy@wolvec.ai" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">privacy@wolvec.ai</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">2. What We Mean by Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        For purposes of this Policy, "consumer health data" means personal information that is linked or reasonably linkable to an individual and that identifies or may reasonably indicate the individual's past, present, or future physical or mental health status, where such information is covered by applicable consumer health data law.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Depending on the context and applicable law, consumer health data may include information a client provides directly, information a coach provides about a client, information generated through the client's use of the Wolvec platform, and health-related inferences or safety flags generated from that information.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Consumer health data does not include deidentified data, publicly available information, or information excluded from coverage under applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">3. Categories of Consumer Health Data We Collect</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may collect the following categories of consumer health data.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.1 Pre-Participation Health Screening Data</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Before using AI-assisted coaching features, clients may be required to complete a pre-participation health screening based on the Physical Activity Readiness Questionnaire for Everyone, commonly known as PAR-Q+.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">This may include responses about:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Exercise readiness</li>
        <li>Known physical limitations</li>
        <li>Cardiovascular, metabolic, renal, or other health conditions relevant to exercise readiness</li>
        <li>Symptoms such as chest pain, dizziness, fainting, shortness of breath, or similar concerns</li>
        <li>Prior injury or illness history relevant to training</li>
        <li>Whether the client has been advised to obtain medical clearance before physical activity</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses this information for safety screening, coach review, and to help ensure that AI-assisted coaching features are not unlocked until the required screening and coach acknowledgment steps are complete.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.2 Injury, Illness, Pain, and Safety Disclosures</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Clients may voluntarily disclose injury, illness, pain, dizziness, symptoms, medication changes, medical appointments, or other health-related information during check-ins, chat interactions, onboarding, or other coaching interactions.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses this information to trigger safety escalation, notify the client's coach, limit AI-generated coaching responses where appropriate, and support appropriate coach follow-up.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.3 Fitness, Training, and Wellness Data</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Wolvec may collect fitness and wellness information, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Fitness goals</li>
        <li>Training history</li>
        <li>Workout logs</li>
        <li>Exercises performed</li>
        <li>Sets, repetitions, weight, duration, distance, or other training metrics</li>
        <li>Rate of perceived exertion</li>
        <li>Program completion records</li>
        <li>Soreness, energy, mood, sleep quality, or similar self-reported wellness indicators</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses this information to support fitness coaching, program personalization, coach review, check-in summaries, and AI-assisted coaching features.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.4 Coaching Conversations and Check-In Responses</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may collect coaching chat messages, check-in responses, and related conversation history. These interactions may include consumer health data if the client discusses physical symptoms, injury, illness, readiness to train, recovery, wellness, or other health-related topics.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses this information to operate the AI-assisted coaching experience, provide summaries and recommendations for coach review, identify safety concerns, and support client-coach communication.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.5 Health Screening Status and Safety Workflow Records</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Wolvec may record safety workflow information, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Whether the client completed health screening</li>
        <li>Whether the coach reviewed or acknowledged the health screening</li>
        <li>Whether the AI-assisted coaching feature is locked or unlocked</li>
        <li>Whether a safety escalation was triggered</li>
        <li>Whether coach follow-up or review is required</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses this information to enforce safety gates, document safety workflow completion, and support legal, audit, compliance, and platform-safety records.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.6 Age Eligibility Information</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec is intended only for users who are at least 18 years old. Wolvec may collect an 18+ attestation, age-confirmation status, or related account information used to enforce age eligibility.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses this information to prevent underage access to AI-assisted coaching features.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">3.7 Health-Related Inferences and Safety Flags</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may generate limited health-related inferences, summaries, or safety flags from client-provided information. For example, the platform may identify that a check-in mentions pain, injury, illness, dizziness, or other symptoms requiring coach attention.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Wolvec uses these inferences and flags for safety escalation, coach review, and platform operation. Wolvec does not use them to diagnose, treat, or provide medical advice.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">4. Sources of Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Wolvec collects consumer health data from the following sources:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Directly from clients during onboarding, health screening, check-ins, chat interactions, and platform use</li>
        <li>From assigned coaches when they provide client context, program information, training limitations, or coaching notes</li>
        <li>From client activity within the Wolvec platform, such as workout completion and check-in history</li>
        <li>From Wolvec's internal systems when generating safety flags, coaching summaries, or workflow status records</li>
        <li>From service providers that process information on Wolvec's behalf to operate the platform</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec does not collect consumer health data from data brokers and does not purchase consumer health data from third parties.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">5. Purposes for Collecting and Using Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Wolvec collects and uses consumer health data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Providing and operating AI-assisted fitness coaching features</li>
        <li>Supporting the relationship between clients and their assigned coach</li>
        <li>Completing pre-participation health screening and safety gating</li>
        <li>Enabling coach review of health screening, check-ins, and safety flags</li>
        <li>Generating AI-assisted program recommendations, check-in summaries, and coaching support</li>
        <li>Personalizing fitness programs, habits, and accountability support</li>
        <li>Detecting and escalating mentions of pain, injury, illness, dizziness, or other safety concerns</li>
        <li>Preventing AI-assisted coaching from continuing when a safety escalation requires human coach review</li>
        <li>Maintaining platform reliability, security, auditability, and compliance</li>
        <li>Responding to user requests, legal requests, security incidents, unauthorized disclosures, or regulatory obligations</li>
        <li>Creating deidentified information for platform improvement, where deidentification standards are satisfied</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec does not use consumer health data for targeted advertising, marketing profiling, sale to data brokers, or unrelated third-party marketing.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">6. How We Share Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may share consumer health data only as described in this Policy, the general Privacy Policy, and the Client Consent.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">6.1 Assigned Coach</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may make a client's consumer health data available to the client's assigned coach. This may include health-screening responses, check-ins, conversations, injury or illness disclosures, safety flags, workout logs, and related coaching context.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Coaching, safety review, program personalization, client follow-up, and coach oversight.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">6.2 AI Model Provider</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may share client health-related coaching content with Anthropic for AI text generation, reasoning, check-in analysis, chat responses, and AI-assisted coaching functionality.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Operating the AI-assisted coaching features requested by the client and coach.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">6.3 Hosting, Database, Infrastructure, and Security Providers</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec uses infrastructure providers to host, secure, transmit, and store platform data. These may include database, hosting, cloud infrastructure, edge security, and platform operations providers.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Platform hosting, storage, security, reliability, data transmission, and platform operations.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">6.4 Error Monitoring and Diagnostics</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec uses error monitoring and diagnostic tools to maintain platform reliability and security. Wolvec configures its systems to exclude message bodies, health-screening responses, health content, session cookies, IP addresses, and other personal information from error-monitoring transmissions where reasonably feasible. Error-monitoring providers may process technical metadata needed for debugging, reliability, and security.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Debugging, reliability, security, and incident response.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">6.5 Push Notification Infrastructure</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may use push notification infrastructure to send generic operational alerts to coaches. These alerts are configured not to include client names, health information, or message content.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Purpose: Operational alerts that route the coach back into the Wolvec platform.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">6.6 Other Service Providers</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may use other service providers for email delivery, support, bug triage, security, and platform operations. These providers may process personal information as described in the general Privacy Policy. Wolvec does not authorize these providers to use consumer health data for unrelated purposes.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">7. Current Named Service Providers</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">As of the Last Updated date, Wolvec uses the following providers in connection with platform operation:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Anthropic: AI text generation, reasoning, check-in analysis, chat responses, and AI-assisted coaching functionality involving client coaching content</li>
        <li>Neon: database storage and managed PostgreSQL infrastructure</li>
        <li>Vercel: hosting and platform operations</li>
        <li>Cloudflare: edge security, DDoS protection, and web application firewall services</li>
        <li>Sentry: error monitoring and performance diagnostics, configured to exclude health content and other personal information where reasonably feasible</li>
        <li>Resend: email delivery for account and agreement communications</li>
        <li>Notion: internal support, bug triage, and product-support workflows where applicable</li>
        <li>Google push notification infrastructure: generic operational coach alerts without client names, health information, or message content</li>
        <li>OpenAI: coach-side voice transcription and coach-methodology embeddings only; based on Wolvec's current architecture, OpenAI does not receive client consumer health data</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec will update this Policy if its service-provider practices materially change.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">8. What Wolvec Does Not Do</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Wolvec does not:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Sell consumer health data</li>
        <li>Share consumer health data for targeted advertising</li>
        <li>Disclose consumer health data to data brokers</li>
        <li>Disclose consumer health data to employers</li>
        <li>Disclose consumer health data to insurance companies</li>
        <li>Use consumer health data for unrelated advertising, retargeting, or marketing profiling</li>
        <li>Use geofencing around healthcare facilities to identify, track, collect data from, or send advertising or notifications to consumers related to healthcare services</li>
        <li>Use individual client conversations to train a generally available AI model</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">9. Consent</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Before collecting consumer health data through client onboarding, health screening, or AI-assisted coaching features, Wolvec presents the relevant disclosures and obtains affirmative consent through the Client Consent and onboarding flow.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Wolvec's consent flow is designed to disclose:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>The categories of consumer health data collected</li>
        <li>The purposes for collection and use</li>
        <li>The categories of entities with whom consumer health data may be shared</li>
        <li>The role of the assigned coach</li>
        <li>The role of service providers</li>
        <li>How consent may be withdrawn</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Withdrawal of consent will prevent Wolvec from continuing to provide AI-assisted coaching features because health screening, safety monitoring, coach review, and AI-assisted coaching require the processing of consumer health data.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Withdrawal does not affect processing that occurred before the withdrawal.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">10. Deidentified Data</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may use deidentified data to improve platform performance, reliability, safety, and design.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec treats data as deidentified only when it cannot reasonably be used to infer information about, or otherwise be linked to, an identified or identifiable individual or device linked to that individual.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        When Wolvec uses deidentified data, Wolvec takes reasonable measures to prevent the data from being associated with an individual, publicly commits to process the data only in deidentified form, and does not attempt to reidentify the data except as permitted by law for testing deidentification effectiveness or security.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If Wolvec shares deidentified data with a recipient, Wolvec will require the recipient to maintain the data in deidentified form and not attempt to reidentify it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">11. Retention</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec retains consumer health data only as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Policy, the general Privacy Policy, the Client Consent, and applicable law.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Current retention periods are:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>PAR-Q+ and health-screening responses: duration of the coaching relationship plus 12 months after account termination</li>
        <li>Injury, illness, pain, or safety disclosures in check-ins: duration of the coaching relationship plus 12 months</li>
        <li>Injury, illness, pain, or safety disclosures in chat: duration of the coaching relationship plus 12 months</li>
        <li>Workout, training, and wellness data: duration of the coaching relationship plus 12 months</li>
        <li>Health-screening status, coach-acknowledgment records, safety flags, and AI unlock status: duration of the account plus 12 months, unless retained longer as a legal, audit, safety, compliance, or dispute-resolution record</li>
        <li>18+ attestation or age-confirmation status: duration of the account plus 12 months</li>
        <li>Backup and audit logs: retained for limited periods consistent with Wolvec's backup, security, and compliance practices</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you request deletion of consumer health data, Wolvec will delete or deidentify consumer health data subject to applicable legal, security, fraud-prevention, backup, dispute-resolution, regulatory-compliance, agreement-enforcement, and recordkeeping obligations.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Where applicable law requires deletion from archived or backup systems, deletion from such systems may be delayed for the period permitted by law.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec may retain limited acceptance and consent records as necessary to document what you agreed to, when you agreed to it, and what agreement, Privacy Policy, Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy, and consent language was shown to you at the time of acceptance.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        These retained records may include your name, email address, account identifier, accepted document version, Privacy Policy version or URL, Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy version or URL, exact agreement text shown at the time of acceptance, exact checkbox text shown, checkbox selections, timestamp, IP address, user agent or browser metadata, acceptance event ID, signature record, document hash or snapshot hash, and related audit logs.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec retains acceptance and consent records for the life of your account plus seven (7) years, or longer if required for a dispute, claim, safety incident, security incident, breach, regulatory inquiry, legal hold, chargeback, threatened claim, or similar matter.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Records retained under this section will be used only for legal, compliance, security, audit, dispute-resolution, agreement-enforcement, or recordkeeping purposes and will not be used for marketing or ordinary product personalization.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">12. Your Consumer Health Data Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Regardless of your state of residence, Wolvec offers the following rights with respect to consumer health data, subject to verification and applicable legal exceptions.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">12.1 Right to Access</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You may request access to the consumer health data Wolvec holds about you.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">12.2 Right to Delete</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You may request deletion of your consumer health data. Wolvec will delete or deidentify consumer health data subject to the retention exceptions described in this Policy and applicable law.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">12.3 Right to Correct</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You may request correction of inaccurate consumer health data.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">12.4 Right to Withdraw Consent</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You may withdraw consent to Wolvec's collection, use, or sharing of consumer health data. Withdrawal will prevent Wolvec from continuing to provide AI-assisted coaching features that require health screening, safety monitoring, coach review, or AI-assisted processing.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">12.5 Right to a List of Third Parties</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You may request a list of third parties and affiliates with whom Wolvec has shared or sold consumer health data, where required by applicable law. Wolvec does not sell consumer health data.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">12.6 Right to Appeal</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Where required by applicable law, you may appeal Wolvec's denial of a consumer health data rights request.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">13. How to Exercise Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">To exercise your consumer health data rights, contact:</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        <a href="mailto:privacy@wolvec.ai" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">privacy@wolvec.ai</a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Use the subject line: Consumer Health Data Request</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Please include:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Your full name</li>
        <li>The email address associated with your Wolvec account</li>
        <li>The specific right you are exercising</li>
        <li>Any information reasonably necessary for Wolvec to verify your identity and locate your account</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec will verify your identity before responding to a request. Wolvec will respond within the timeframe required by applicable law. Where permitted by law, Wolvec may extend the response period when reasonably necessary due to the complexity or number of requests.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If Wolvec cannot verify your identity using commercially reasonable efforts, Wolvec may request additional information reasonably necessary to authenticate the request.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Wolvec will not discriminate against you for exercising your consumer health data rights.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">14. Washington State Residents</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you are a Washington State resident or your consumer health data is collected in Washington, your consumer health data may be protected by the Washington My Health My Data Act.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This Policy is intended to serve as Wolvec's consumer health data privacy policy for Washington purposes.
      </p>
